The paper is about visual tracking, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new algorithm that uses adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The algorithm also uses a generative network to augment positive samples, which involves generating new data, a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed algorithm on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO) research.
